&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: Theatre Health Care Assistant at Bedford &lt;strong&gt;Satellite&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours p/w: Full time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift pattern: Flexible including weekends and late shifts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band: Band 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Moorfields is recognised as one of the best ophthalmic eye hospitals in the world and we pride ourselves on the professionalism of our nurses and the quality of the nursing care we provide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Moorfields at Bedford offers a comprehensive ophthalmic service to our patients in Bedfordshire and surrounding areas. We are looking for theatre staff to provide a comprehensive Moorfields theatre team for our patients. We are looking to recruit a theatre health care assistant to support our ophthalmic theatre staff in providing a holistic approach to ophthalmic care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have a wide interest in caring for ophthalmic patients in the theatre pathway. This is an opportunity to join our dynamic team of ophthalmic nursing staff and theatre practitioners and develop your skills further both in theatre and in the clinical setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate must have an NVQ level 3 qualification or relevant clinical theatre experience. The successful candidates will be required to be flexible, enthusiastic and committed to bringing the highest level of theatre care to patients in line with the Quality Agenda of the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Personnel Department can be contacted on 0207 566 2433/2864 Monday to Friday from 9:15am – 5pm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Namemary jane casalme Job title Sister Email address maryjane.casalme@bedfordhospital.nhs.uk Telephone number 01234355122 ext 2348 / 5341 Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For an informal discussion please contact Maryjane.casalme@bedfordhospital.nhs.uk &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;telephone# 01234355122 ext 2348/5341&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
